Make clucene library from source codes:
    mkdir clucene
    cd clucene
    cvs -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/clucene login
    (Just press Enter when it asks for password)
    cvs -z3 -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/clucene co -P clucene
    sh bootstrap
    sh configure --prefix=/usr/local
    make
    sudo make install

Make a Lucene index directory for dict.txt
    g++ -O2 -I/usr/local/include -I../../Headers -L/usr/local/lib -lclucene ../../Experiments/Lucene4SpellChecker/LuceneAdd.cpp ../../Source/OVFileHandler.cpp ../../Source/OVStringToolKit.cpp -o createLuceneIndex4Dict
    ./createLuceneIndex4Dict
    (This step take 6 mins on my PowerBook 1G)
    sudo cp -fpR indexDir /Library/OpenVanilla/0.7.0/Modules/OVIMRomanNew/
    
Then go to make and install OVIMRomanNew